      "ctx": "A student wrote: \"Yesterday I have visited the new museum in town. It was very interesting and I have learned a lot about local history.\"",
      "v": "(a) Find two grammatical errors in the student's writing and correct them.\n(b) Explain the rule that applies.",
      "o": [
       ""
      ],
      "c": 0,
      "u": "(a) \"I have visited\" → \"I visited\" (yesterday = finished past time marker → simple past). \"I have learned\" → \"I learned\" (same reason). (b) Present perfect is used for experiences without a specific time OR for actions with present relevance. When a finished past time expression is present (yesterday, last year, in 2020), simple past must be used."
